    </div>

    <!-- SEO Content Section -->
    <div class="seo-content">
      <h2>The Evolution of Free-to-Play Gaming</h2>
      <p>Gone are the days when "free-to-play" (F2P) meant low-quality, pay-to-win browser games. Today, the most played, most profitable, and most competitive games on the planet utilize the F2P model. Developers have realized that removing the barrier to entry allows for massive player bases, which sustains matchmaking ecosystems and drives long-term revenue through cosmetics and battle passes.</p>

      <h2>How Do Free Games Make Money?</h2>
      <p>Understanding monetization is crucial before investing hundreds of hours into a F2P title. The games on this list generally fall into three categories:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Pure Cosmetics (e.g., Valorant, Fortnite):</strong> The gold standard. You cannot buy an advantage. Revenue is generated purely through weapon skins, character outfits, and battle passes.</li>
        <li><strong>Pay for Convenience / Roster (e.g., League of Legends, Apex Legends, Path of Exile):</strong> While gameplay remains fair, you can pay to unlock characters faster, or in POE's case, buy inventory space to make inventory management less tedious.</li>
        <li><strong>Gacha / Pay to Progress (e.g., Genshin Impact):</strong> Heavily relies on random chance to unlock characters and weapons. While entirely playable for free, paying money directly accelerates your power and progress.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Choosing the Right Game For You</h2>
      <p>If you're looking for high-stakes competition and have the patience to learn, tactical shooters like <strong>Valorant</strong> or MOBAs like <strong>League of Legends</strong> offer endless depth. If you prefer solo grinding and theory-crafting, <strong>Path of Exile</strong> is unrivaled. For a more relaxed, narrative-driven experience (provided you can resist the gambling mechanics), <strong>Genshin Impact</strong> provides AAA quality for zero upfront cost.</p>
    </div>

    
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
const searchInput = document.getElementById('searchInput');
    const filterBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn');
    const gameCards = document.querySelectorAll('.game-card');
    const gamesGrid = document.getElementById('gamesGrid');

    // Create no results message element
    const noResultsMsg = document.createElement('div');
    noResultsMsg.className = 'no-results hidden';
    noResultsMsg.textContent = 'No games found matching your criteria.';
    gamesGrid.appendChild(noResultsMsg);

    let currentFilter = 'all';
    let currentSearch = '';

    function filterGames() {
      let visibleCount = 0;

      gameCards.forEach(card => {
        const tags = card.getAttribute('data-tags').toLowerCase();
        const textContent = card.textContent.toLowerCase();

        const matchesSearch = currentSearch === '' ||
                              textContent.includes(currentSearch) ||
                              tags.includes(currentSearch);

        const matchesFilter = currentFilter === 'all' ||
                              tags.includes(currentFilter);

        if (matchesSearch && matchesFilter) {
          card.classList.remove('hidden');
          visibleCount++;
        } else {
          card.classList.add('hidden');
        }
      });

      if (visibleCount === 0) {
        noResultsMsg.classList.remove('hidden');
      } else {
        noResultsMsg.classList.add('hidden');
      }
    }

    // Search input listener
    searchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
      currentSearch = e.target.value.toLowerCase().trim();
      filterGames();
    });

    // Filter buttons listener
    filterBtns.forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        // Update active class
        filterBtns.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
        btn.classList.add('active');

        // Update filter state and run
        currentFilter = btn.getAttribute('data-filter');
        filterGames();
      });
    });
